# C# Patterns

## Controllers
- Use `[ApiController]` and `[Route("api/[controller]")]`
- Authorize with `[Authorize(Roles = nameof(UserRole.XXX))]`
- Return `ActionResult<T>` for typed responses
- Extract user ID via `User.FindFirstValue(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier)`

## Entity Framework
- Use `AsNoTracking()` for read-only queries
- Always include `CancellationToken ct` parameter
- Configure precision for decimal: `HasPrecision(18, 2)`
- Use `OnDelete(DeleteBehavior.Restrict)` to prevent cascade issues

## Services
- Define interface `IXxxService` and implementation `XxxService`
- Register as `AddScoped<IXxxService, XxxService>()` in `Program.cs`
- Use `IHttpClientFactory` for external API calls (named clients)
- Use `IDbContextFactory<AppDbContext>` when service needs independent DB scope

## Error Handling
- Use `logger.LogError(ex, "message {Param}", param)` with structured logging
- Return `BadRequest("message")` for validation errors
- Return `NotFound("message")` for missing entities
